	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Emulator license?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- Since I'm near to release RockNES 5.00, I'd like to discuss ideas about a license of usage. You know the thrill, as "do not package commercial ROM images" or "use it at your own risk". Of course this looks basic and perhaps use/meaningless..?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Sun Mar 15, 2009 4:59 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are two main things a license achieves:
<br />- Exerts whatever control you want over your work. Like whether it's sold, can be modified/derived from, etc.
<br />- Protects you from legal issues when people misuse it, for example running a life support system via an emulated NES cartridge.
<br />
<br />So to select a license, you have to decide what control you want to exert, and what legal issues you're concerned about.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sun Mar 15, 2009 5:03 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />"Be aware that popular NES games are copyrighted with all rights reserved. In most cases, distributing ROM images of these games infringes copyright. Do not distribute RockNES software along with infringing ROMs."
<br />
<br />Beyond that, the wording of a software copyright license depends on exactly what you want to allow, as blargg pointed out. Before you draft the license text, you should decide whether to: <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>include or not include source code </li><li>allow or forbid distribution of copies of the emulator from mirror sites </li><li>allow or forbid distribution of copies of the emulator <a href="http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/selling.html" class="postlink">for a fee</a> </li><li>allow or forbid distribution of copies of the emulator bundled with a ROM with consent of the ROM's copyright owner, as is done in Wii Shop Channel </li></ol>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


